A client and server written in Python.
Written by Tyler Hanlon


Currently provides minimal UI.

~Commandline Arguments~

warlord_client:
  -s -- Change the host name/IP address to the next argument
  -p -- Change the port to the next argument
  -n -- Try to join the server with your name as the next argument
  -m -- Manual mode (takes plays from players)
  -q -- Used for debugging (causes client to quit as soon as it confirms it has joined)

warlord_server:
  -l -- The time between the lobby having enough to start a game and the game starting
  -m -- Changes the minimum player number to the next argument
  -t -- Changes the time allowed for a player to take on their turn before sending a strike
